    "The table below summarizes and categorizes these types.",
    "Assessing risk and return within a target asset allocation often relies on a rebalancing strategy.",
    "This approach considers the frequency of portfolio reviews, acknowledging it as a factor influencing whether the portfolio's actual performance aligns with its intended asset allocation.",
    "The core objective of rebalancing is to manage risk concerning the target asset allocation, prioritizing risk management over solely maximizing returns.",
    "Investors typically choose a rebalancing strategy based on their risk tolerance about expected returns, factoring in rebalancing costs (Zilbering et al., 2015)."
